aining\", \"from\": 3829, \"to\": 3843}, {\"ngram\": \"private commercial interests\", \"from\": 3855, \"to\": 3883}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Zhang gave the example ofdaipai, or paparazzi, where independent photographers might create a public nuisance in order to take photos of sports stars to sell to fan groups - a phenomenon which he said has worsened in recent years.\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 4168, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mr Zhang\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 3943}, {\"ngram\": \"the example ofdaipai\", \"from\": 3949, \"to\": 3969}, {\"ngram\": \"paparazzi\", \"from\": 3974, \"to\": 3983}, {\"ngram\": \"independent photographers\", \"from\": 3991, \"to\": 4016}, {\"ngram\": \"a public nuisance\", \"from\": 4030, \"to\": 4047}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4056}, {\"ngram\": \"photos\", \"from\": 4065, \"to\": 4071}, {\"ngram\": \"sports stars\", \"from\": 4075, \"to\": 4087}, {\"ngram\": \"fan groups\", \"from\": 4099, \"to\": 4109}, {\"ngram\": \"a phenomenon\", \"from\": 4112, \"to\": 4124}, {\"ngram\": \"recent years\", \"from\": 4155, \"to\": 4167}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Associate Professor Xi Zhiwu, from the School of Journalism and Communication at Nanchang University in Jiangxi province, believes that the ability of China's sports authority to improve the image of Chinese fans islimited.\", \"from\": 4170, \"to\": 4393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4274, \"end\": 4281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jiangxi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.822388133029196e-23, \"text\": \"Jiangxi\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jiangxi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jiangxi\"}, {\"begin\": 4321, \"end\": 4326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999981513100273, \"rank\": 1.7188565826678292e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 4370, \"end\": 4377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9650935395265409, \"rank\": 0.03592158159591428, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Associate Professor Xi Zhiwu\", \"from\": 4170, \"to\": 4198}, {\"ngram\": \"the School\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4215}, {\"ngram\": \"Journalism\", \"from\": 4219, \"to\": 4229}, {\"ngram\": \"Communication\", \"from\": 4234, \"to\": 4247}, {\"ngram\": \"Nanchang University\", \"from\": 4251, \"to\": 4270}, {\"ngram\": \"the ability\", \"from\": 4306, \"to\": 4317}, {\"ngram\": \"the image\", \"from\": 4357, \"to\": 4366}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It also cannot really change how much fans worship their idols.\", \"from\": 4395, \"to\": 4459, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"how much fans\", \"from\": 4425, \"to\": 4438}, {\"ngram\": \"their idols\", \"from\": 4447, \"to\": 4458}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is only trying to guide fans to follow competitive sports and its stars in a reasonable, rational and healthy way,\\\" said Prof Xi, who has studied the growth of fan culture in China.\", \"from\": 4460, \"to\": 4644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4638, \"end\": 4643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999981513100273, \"rank\": 1.7188565826678292e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 4487, \"to\": 4491}, {\"ngram\": \"competitive sports\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4520}, {\"ngram\": \"its stars\", \"from\": 4525, \"to\": 4534}, {\"ngram\": \"a reasonable, rational and healthy way\", \"from\": 4538, \"to\": 4576}, {\"ngram\": \"Prof Xi\", \"from\": 4584, \"to\": 4591}, {\"ngram\": \"the growth\", \"from\": 4609, \"to\": 4619}, {\"ngram\": \"fan culture\", \"from\": 4623, \"to\": 4634}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But \\\"fan culture\\\" should not be seen as a derogatory term, he said, adding that he does not see the zeal that Chinese fans have for their sports stars as different from those in other countries.\", \"from\": 4646, \"to\": 4840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4756, \"end\": 4763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9650935395265409, \"rank\": 0.03592158159591428, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"fan culture\", \"from\": 4650, \"to\": 4662}, {\"ngram\": \"a derogatory term\", \"from\": 4686, \"to\": 4703}, {\"ngram\": \"the zeal\", \"from\": 4742, \"to\": 4750}, {\"ngram\": \"their sports stars\", \"from\": 4778, \"to\": 4796}, {\"ngram\": \"other countries\", \"from\": 4824, \"to\": 4839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Yin Yiyi of Beijing Normal University said highly commercialised sports in other countries, from football to e-sports, have led to mature fan management systems, such as official fan clubs.\", \"from\": 4842, \"to\": 5034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4845, \"end\": 4848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feng_shui\", \"score\": 0.9464324589198732, \"rank\": 0.0565994334932255, \"text\": \"Yin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feng_shui\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feng_shui\"}, {\"begin\": 4857, \"end\": 4882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing_Normal_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beijing Normal University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing_Normal_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing_Normal_University\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"highly commercialised sports\", \"from\": 4888, \"to\": 4916}, {\"ngram\": \"other countries\", \"from\": 4920, \"to\": 4935}, {\"ngram\": \"football\", \"from\": 4942, \"to\": 4950}, {\"ngram\": \"e\", \"from\": 4954, \"to\": 4955}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4956, \"to\": 4962}, {\"ngram\": \"fan management systems\", \"from\": 4983, \"to\": 5005}, {\"ngram\": \"official fan clubs\", \"from\": 5015, \"to\": 5033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The long tradition of Western sports fans and the high degree of commercialisation means it is easier to manage and cultivate fans, said Dr Yin, who researches fan and popular culture.\", \"from\": 5036, \"to\": 5220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5176, \"end\": 5179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feng_shui\", \"score\": 0.9464324589198732, \"rank\": 0.0565994334932255, \"text\": \"Yin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feng_shui\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feng_shui\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The long tradition\", \"from\": 5036, \"to\": 5054}, {\"ngram\": \"Western sports fans\", \"from\": 5058, \"to\": 5077}, {\"ngram\": \"the high degree\", \"from\": 5082, \"to\": 5097}, {\"ngram\": \"commercialisation\", \"from\": 5101, \"to\": 5118}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 5162, \"to\": 5166}, {\"ngram\": \"fan\", \"from\": 5196, \"to\": 5199}, {\"ngram\": \"popular culture\", \"from\": 5204, \"to\": 5219}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Although such Western sports fan culture also has problems such as name-calling, therulesto manage them are relatively clear,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 5222, \"to\": 5359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5237, \"end\": 5244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9999961428840642, \"rank\": 3.857130853799878e-06, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"problems\", \"from\": 5273, \"to\": 5281}, {\"ngram\": \"therulesto\", \"from\": 5304, \"to\": 5314}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Comparatively, in China, there is almost no tradition of competitive sports fans, and the early football and basketball fan bases were not large, she said.China's professional national football league kicked off 30 years ago, in 1994, and the Chinese Basketball Association league was founded a year later.\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5379, \"end\": 5384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999981513100273, \"rank\": 1.7188565826678292e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 5604, \"end\": 5634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.128457891662151e-34, \"text\": \"Chinese Basketball Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Basketball_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"almost no tradition\", \"from\": 5395, \"to\": 5414}, {\"ngram\": \"competitive sports fans\", \"from\": 5418, \"to\": 5441}, {\"ngram\": \"the early football and basketball fan bases\", \"from\": 5447, \"to\": 5490}, {\"ngram\": \"China's professional national football league\", \"from\": 5516, \"to\": 5561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fan and support culture was almost entirely introduced by idol culture in the entertainment field.\", \"from\": 5669, \"to\": 5767, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fan\", \"from\": 5669, \"to\": 5672}, {\"ngram\": \"support culture\", \"from\": 5677, \"to\": 5692}, {\"ngram\": \"idol culture\", \"from\": 5727, \"to\": 5739}, {\"ngram\": \"the entertainment field\", \"from\": 5743, \"to\": 5766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Concepts such as ensuring their idols are trending on social media and pseudo-intimacy between fans and idols are brought to competitive athletes, making it more difficult to manage,\\\" added Dr Yin.\", \"from\": 5768, \"to\": 5966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5962, \"end\": 5965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feng_shui\", \"score\": 0.9464324589198732, \"rank\": 0.0565994334932255, \"text\": \"Yin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feng_shui\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feng_shui\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Concepts\", \"from\": 5769, \"to\": 5777}, {\"ngram\": \"their idols\", \"from\": 5795, \"to\": 5806}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 5823, \"to\": 5835}, {\"ngram\": \"pseudo\", \"from\": 5840, \"to\": 5846}, {\"ngram\": \"intimacy\", \"from\": 5847, \"to\": 5855}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 5864, \"to\": 5868}, {\"ngram\": \"idols\", \"from\": 5873, \"to\": 5878}, {\"ngram\": \"competitive athletes\", \"from\": 5894, \"to\": 5914}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Zhang, a long-time industry observer, said that as public figures, athletes also have to bear a share of the responsibility, in how they conduct themselves and guide fans on the right behaviour.\", \"from\": 5968, \"to\": 6165, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mr Zhang\", \"from\": 5968, \"to\": 5976}, {\"ngram\": \"a long-time industry observer\", \"from\": 5978, \"to\": 6007}, {\"ngram\": \"public figures\", \"from\": 6022, \"to\": 6036}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 6038, \"to\": 6046}, {\"ngram\": \"a share\", \"from\": 6065, \"to\": 6072}, {\"ngram\": \"the responsibility\", \"from\": 6076, \"to\": 6094}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 6137, \"to\": 6141}, {\"ngram\": \"the right behaviour\", \"from\": 6145, \"to\": 6164}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For instance, they can influence fans on how to best express their views on competition results, promote the principle of sportsmanship and how best to accept wins and defeats.\\\"\", \"from\": 6167, \"to\": 6345, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"